      </fig>
      <p>By comparing a large collection of previous models of the Calvin-Benson cycle, Arnold and Nikoloski created a quantitative consensus model that comprises eleven species, six reactions, and one assignment rule
[<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="B36">36</xref>]. All kinetic equations within this model call specialized function definitions. Figure <xref ref-type="fig" rid="F8">8</xref> shows the simulation results for the species ribulose-1,5-bisphosphate, ATP, and ADP within this model. As in the previous test case, the dynamics computed by the Simulation Core Library reproduce the figures provided by BioModels Database.</p>
